<div class="mod-page plain"><div>
	<h2>$.presentation is ...</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>the presentation framework based on jQuery.</li>
		<li>works on the browsers without IE6,7</li>
		<li>looks pretty cool if your browser is webkit based.</li>
		<li>You can use this template and script for any use.</li>
		<li>I'm happy if you put some notes or link about this framework somewhere on your presentation.</li>
		<li><a href="http://code.google.com/p/jquery-presentation/">project page</a></li>
	</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="mod-page plain"><div>
	<h2>Keyboard shortcuts</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Left,Up arrow / PgUp: prev page</li>
		<li>Right,Down arrow / PgDn: next page</li>
		<li>Home: first page</li>
		<li>End: last page</li>
	</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="mod-page plain"><div>
	<h2>Tips</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>add &lt;div class=&quot;mod-page&quot;&gt; to create pages.</li>
		<li>Create your own page template to add the skin class to this div.<br />ex) &lt;div class=&quot;mod-page mySkin&quot;&gt;</li>
		<li>Write css under your skin class.<br />see the example in "common.css".<br />You can find "plain" and "shout" skin there.</li>
		<li>Add the class "first" to the &lt;div class=&quot;mod-page&quot;&gt;<br />which you want to show first.</li>
		<li>If no "div.mod-page.first" found,<br />$.presentation shows the first "div.mod-page".</li>
	</ul>
</div></div>

